## This lecture emphasizes the critical importance of protecting Personally Identifiable Information (PII) and the potential consequences of failing to do so.

## Handling and Storing PII

- It is crucial to be deliberate about how PII is handled and stored, always knowing its location.
- Protecting PII may be legally required to comply with various regulations and laws.

## Consequences of Non-Compliance

- Failure to meet PII obligations can lead to government regulators investigating company practices.
- Customers and businesses may directly inquire about data handling, impacting customer relationships.

## Staying Informed and Seeking Advice

- Keep up-to-date with PII compliance, regulations, and laws by consulting relevant government websites in the applicable jurisdiction.
- Due to the complexity and varied nature of PII laws globally, it is important to seek legal counsel for specific questions.
